    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "100 MB of memory is quite a lot, and I think plenty of Qt code doesn't need a web engine, e.g. matplotlib's Qt backend probably doesn't.\r\n\r\nMaybe an easy if ugly workaround is to make a `%gui qt5-web` option that loads QWebEngine."
